# Turning Point USA 'All American' Halftime Show Lineup Revealed: Who’s Performing at the Rival Super Bowl Event
Authored by: [Naman Trivedi](https://www.timesnownews.com/author/naman-trivedi-479268085)Updated Oct 9, 2025, 23:40 IST
Turning Point USA has announced "The All American Halftime Show" as a rival event to the official Super Bowl LX halftime show featuring Bad Bunny. The alternative performance, set for February 8, 2026, will aim to offer a culturally conservative counterpoint.Bad Bunny
Photo : AP[follow us](https://news.google.com/publications/CAAqBwgKMK-p_Qowq-D0Ag?hl=en-IN&gl=IN&ceid=IN:en)[follow us](https://whatsapp.com/channel/0029Va7R81560eBdf7e61g0T)In a bold move that’s stirring political and cultural conversation, Turning Point USA has officially announced it will host an alternate halftime show during Super Bowl LX, set for February 8, 2026, at Levi’s Stadium in Santa Clara, California. Branded as “The All American Halftime Show,” this parallel broadcast will go head-to-head with the NFL’s main event performance by Puerto Rican superstar Bad Bunny, who has drawn sharp backlash from conservative circles.
## Why a Rival Halftime Show?
The announcement comes amid online controversy following the NFL’s decision to book Bad Bunny, a three-time Grammy winner and one of the world’s most streamed artists, as the headline act.
